" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 485px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Mallinckrodt esophageal tracheal airway double lumen (Combitube) insertion",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 465px; height: 605px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    A. Lubricate and insert the Combitube until the double black line is located in between the teeth. B. Inflate the blue pharyngeal cuff and white pilot balloons. C. Attach bag-valve-mask to the blue connector and assess for lung sounds and chest wall movement. Pass a gastric tube through the white distall connector and confirm suction of gastric contents. D. If&nbsp;breath sounds and chest wall movement are absent or decreased, the distal balloon may be in the trachea. Place &nbsp;the bag-valve-mask on the connector for the white distal balloon and ventilate.",
